21.07.09), Apostolic Administrator of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Malta|Diocese of Malta]] ([[Malta]]) (1516.05.23 \u2013 1520), Apostolic Administrator of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Lucca|Diocese of Lucca]] (Italy) (1517.03.09 \u2013 1517.11.12), ?again Cardinal-Bishop of Ostia\u2013Velletri (?1517.07.24 \u2013 death 1521.07.09), Apostolic Administrator of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Malaga|Diocese of Malaga]] (Balearic Spain) (1518.04.12 \u2013 1518.09.03), again Apostolic Administrator of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Pisa|Archdiocese of Pisa]] (Italy) (1518.09.03 \u2013 retired 1518.09.10) \n* [[Alfonso de Fonseca]] (1493 \u2013 death 1505), previously Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of \u00c1vila|\u00c1vila]] (Spain) (1469\u20131485), Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Cuenca|Cuenca]] (Spain) (1485\u20131493)\n** [[Auxiliary Bishop]]: Garc\u00eda de Chinchilla, O.P. (1500.09.18 \u2013 death 1502), [[Titular Bishop]] of [[Byblus]] (1500.09.18 \u2013 1502)\n* [[Alfonso Enr\u00edquez]] (19 December 1505 \u2013 death 15 October 1523)\n** [[Auxiliary Bishop]]: Blas de Fernando, [[Cistercian Order]] (O. Cist.- (1507.04.19 \u2013 ?), Titular Bishop of above Byblus (1507.04.19 \u2013 ?)\n* [[Juan Pardo Tavera]] (31 December 1523 \u2013 8 June 1524), previously Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Ciudad Rodrigo|Ciudad Rodrigo]] (Spain) (1514.07.14 \u2013 1523.12.31); later Metropolitan Archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Santiago de Compostela|Santiago de Compostela]] (Spain) (1524.06.08 \u2013retired 1534.04.27), created [[Cardinal-Priest]] of [[S. Giovanni a Porta Latina]] (1531.04.27 \u2013 death 1545.08.01), Metropolitan Archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Toledo|Toledo]] (Spain) (1534.04.27 \u2013 1545.08.01)\n* [[Garc\u00eda de Loaysa y Mendoza]], [[Order of Preachers]] (O.P.) (8 June 1524 \u2013 23 February 1532), previously Master of the [[Dominican Order]] (O.P.) (1518.05.23 \u2013 1524.06.08), created [[Cardinal-Priest]] of [[S. Susanna]] (1530.05.16 \u2013 death 1546.04.22), Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Sig\u00fcenza|Sig\u00fcenza]] (Spain) (1532.02.23 \u2013 1539.05.21), Metropolitan Archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Sevilla|Sevilla]] (Spain) (1539.05.21 \u2013 1546.04.22)\n* [[Pedro Gonz\u00e1lez Manso]] (13 March 1532 \u2013 death 12 February 1537), previously Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Guadix|Guadix]] (Spain) (1523.08.31 \u2013 1524.10.26), Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tui|Tui]] (Spain) (1524.10.26 \u2013 1525.07.03), Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Badajoz|Badajoz]] (Spain) (1525.07.03 \u2013 1532.03.13)\n* [[Pedro Alvarez de Acosta]] (21 May 1539 \u2013 death 20 February 1563), previously Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Porto|Porto]] (Portugal) (1507.02.12 \u2013 1535.01.08), Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Le\u00f3n in Spain|Le\u00f3n]] (Spain) (1535.01.08 \u2013 1539.05.21)\n* [[Honorato Juan]] (1 March 1564 \u2013 death 30 July 1566)\n* [[Francisco Tello Sandoval]] (3 March 1567 \u2013 13 June 1578), next Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Plasencia|Plasencia]] (Spain) (1578.06.13 \u2013 death 1580.07.08)\n* [[Alonso Vel\u00e1zquez]] (13 June 1578 \u2013 9 March 1583), next Metropolitan Archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Santiago de Compostela|Santiago de Compostela]] (Spain) (1583.03.09 \u2013 death 1587.01.14)\n* [[Sebasti\u00e1n P\u00e9rez (bishop)]] (9 May 1583 \u2013 death 27 July 1593 Died)\n* [[Mart\u00edn Garnica]] (27 April 1594 \u2013 death 20 November 1594 Died)<ref name=HierarchiaIV>{{cite book|url=http://sul-derivatives.stanford.edu/derivative?CSNID=00002719&mediaType=application/pdf|last1=Gauchat|first1=Patritius (Patrice)|title=HIERARCHIA CATHOLICA MEDII ET RECENTIORIS AEVI Vol IV|pages=268|date=1935|publisher=Libraria Regensbergiana|location=M\u00fcnster|ISBN=}} ''(in Latin)''</ref>\n* [[Pedro Rojas Henr\u00edques]], [[Order of Saint Augustine]] (O.S.A.) (30 August 1595 \u2013 death 9 March 1602), previously Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Astorga|Astorga]] (Spain) (1591.03.06 \u2013 1595.08.30)\n* Enrique Enr\u00edquez, O.E.S.A. (1602.11.15 \u2013 1610.06.21), next Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Plasencia|Plasencia]] (Spain) (1610.06.21 \u2013 death 1622.01.22)\n* [[Fernando Acevedo Gonz\u00e1lez]] (July 1610 \u2013 2 June 1613), next Metropolitan Archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Burgos|Burgos]] (Spain) (1613.06.02 \u2013 1629)\n* [[Francisco de Sosa]], O.F.M. (23 September 1613 \u2013 death 1618)<ref name=HierarchiaIV />\n* [[Crist\u00f3bal de Lobera y Torres]] (9 July 1618 \u2013 6 March 1623)<ref name=HierarchiaIV />\n* [[Alsono Mart\u00edn de Zu\u00f1iga]] (23 March 1623 \u2013 21 June 1630 Died)<ref name=HierarchiaIV />\n* [[Domingo Pimentel Z\u00fa\u00f1iga]], [[Order of Preachers|O.P.]] (2 October 1630 \u2013 18 July 1633)<ref name=HierarchiaIV />\n* [[Francisco Villafa\u00f1e]] (5 September 1633 \u2013 26 August 1639 Died)<ref name=HierarchiaIV />\n* [[Mart\u00edn Carrillo Alderete]] (9 June 1636 \u2013 1 July 1641)<ref name=HierarchiaIV /><ref name=CathHierMartCarrAld>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bcaral.html \"Archbishop Mart\u00edn Carrillo Alderete\"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved September 17, 2016 [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref>\n* [[Antonio Vald\u00e9s Herrera]] (21 October 1641 \u2013 10 November 1653)<ref name=HierarchiaIV /><ref name=CathHierAntValHerr>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bvaldh.html \"Bishop Antonio Vald\u00e9s Herrera\"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved September 17, 2016 [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref>\n* [[Juan de Palafox y Mendoza]] (24 November 1653 \u2013 1 October 1659 Died)<ref name=HierarchiaIV />\n* [[Nicol\u00e1s Martinez (bishop)]], [[O.S.H.]] (21 June 1660 \u2013 1 Oct 1660 Died)<ref name=HierarchiaIV />\n* [[Alfonso Enr\u00edquez de Santo Tom\u00e1s]], [[Order of Preachers|O.P.]] (26 Sep 1661 \u2013 28 Jan 1664 Confirmed, [[Bishop of Plasencia]])<ref name=HierarchiaIV />\n* [[Pedro de Godoy]], [[Order of Preachers|O.P.]] (31 March 1664 \u2013 16 May 1672 Confirmed, [[Bishop of Sig\u00fcenza]])<ref name=HierarchiaIV /> \n* [[Antonio de Isla y Mena]] (8 August 1672 \u2013 17 Dec 1681 Died) \n* [[Sebasti\u00e1n de Ar\u00e9valo y Torres]], [[Order of Friars Minor]] (O.F.M.) (20 April 1682 \u2013 20 Jan 1704 Died)\n* [[Jorge C\u00e1rdenas Valenzuela]] (1704 \u2013 18 November 1705 Died)\n* [[Andr\u00e9s Soto de la Fuente]] (22 March 1706 \u2013 29 December 1714 Died)\n* [[Felipe Antonio Gil Taboada]] (5 July 1715 \u2013 4 March 1720)\n* [[Miguel Herrero Esgueva]] (15 April 1720 \u2013 20 January 1723)\n* [[Jacinto Valledor Fresno]] (12 April 1723 \u2013 12 February 1730 Died)\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Barnuevo]], O.S.B. (24 July 1730 \u2013 25 July 1735 Died)\n* [[Pedro de la Cuadra Achica]] (1 April 1736 \u2013 7 September 1741)\n* [[Juan Antonio Oru\u00f1a]]  (28 September 1744 \u2013 4 March 1748 Died)\n* [[Pedro Clemente de Ar\u00f3stegui]] (16 September 1747 \u2013 29 August 1760)\n* [[Jacinto Aguado y Chac\u00f3n]] (18 July 1762 \u2013 27 March 1764)\n* [[Bernardo Antonio Calder\u00f3n L\u00e1zaro]] (20 August 1764 \u2013 15 October 1786)\n* [[Joaqu\u00edn de Eleta]], O.F.M. (27 December 1786 \u2013 4 December 1788 Died)\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Constancio Andino]] (29 March 1790 \u2013 death Nov 1793)\n* [[Diego Melo Portugal]], [[Order of Saint Augustine]] (O.S.A.) (12 September 1794 \u2013 18 December 1795)\n* [[Antonio Tavira Almaz\u00e1n]] (27 June 1796 \u2013 14 August 1798)\n* [[Francisco Ignacio I\u00f1igo Angulo]] (25 September 1798 \u2013 8 January 1799)\n* [[Juan Moya (bishop)|Juan Moya]], O.F.M. (28 March 1799 \u2013 19 February 1801)\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Antonio Garnica]], [[Capuchin Franciscans]] (O.F.M. Cap.) (23 February 1801 \u2013 10 January 1810)\n* [[Juan Cavia Gonz\u00e1lez]] (19 August 1814 \u2013 23 December 1831)\n* [[Gregorio S\